            <p facs="#facs_80_tr_2">
               <lb facs="#facs_80_tr_2_tl_1" n="N001"/>tsn
               <lb facs="#facs_80_tr_2_tl_2" n="N002"/>lʼauteur ses
               <lb facs="#facs_80_tr_2_tl_3" n="N003"/>-467.
               <lb facs="#facs_80_tr_2_tl_4" n="N004"/>metaphysical questions by a definition. Every child can put to Lea-me those Ihilos congress whoény
               <lb facs="#facs_80_tr_2_tl_5" n="N005"/>philos kvphy. (litfte laughter). Now these questions, even if the children do not ask them actually,
               <lb facs="#facs_80_tr_2_tl_6" n="N006"/>are IN the children-veryisserently but they all have their life problems. They have their
               <lb facs="#facs_80_tr_2_tl_7" n="N007"/>probiems that some things they would LIBE to have, they CANNOT get; that some things they don’t
               <lb facs="#facs_80_tr_2_tl_8" n="N008"/>like to do, they MUST do; that other things give them joy, if they are doing them; that there is a
               <lb facs="#facs_80_tr_2_tl_9" n="N009"/>hostility they feel very early in the love of their mother, or in the hestility in themselves against a
               <lb facs="#facs_80_tr_2_tl_10" n="N010"/>younger brother or sister; there are difficulties of getting friends—there are all kinds of problem
               <lb facs="#facs_80_tr_2_tl_11" n="N011"/>in every child. There are very early, often, krotic lproblems. Now all problem are there.
               <lb facs="#facs_80_tr_2_tl_12" n="N012"/>You are able, if you have very little bit insight into the human soul (and we have today much
            </p>
            <p facs="#facs_80_tr_3">
               <lb facs="#facs_80_tr_3_tl_1" n="N001"/>possilibities of these insight) to know where the questions lie if you observe a child. And then,
               <lb facs="#facs_80_tr_3_tl_2" n="N002"/>even if the question is not formalated—and very rarely will it be formulated—it CAN be got out;
               <lb facs="#facs_80_tr_3_tl_3" n="N003"/>you can find out; you can bring it into consciousness. And to these questions the religious symbols
               <lb facs="#facs_80_tr_3_tl_4" n="N004"/>are the answers. And all these questions have something to do with the fundamental question of
               <lb facs="#facs_80_tr_3_tl_5" n="N005"/>finitude, to which God is the answer; or the fundamental question of etuilt feeling, to wch
               <lb facs="#facs_80_tr_3_tl_6" n="N006"/>reconciliation, ororgiveness, is the answer.
               <lb facs="#facs_80_tr_3_tl_7" n="N007"/>Now this CAN BE DONE, and ONLy if these questions are alive and are brought into
            </p>
            <p facs="#facs_80_tr_1">
               <lb facs="#facs_80_tr_1_tl_1" n="N001"/>consciousness do the answers have a meaning. I otherwise the answers are simply stuff, dead material,
               <lb facs="#facs_80_tr_1_tl_2" n="N002"/>to be taken in, and have no meaning whatsoever. But here again we are in the problem of introduction.
               <lb facs="#facs_80_tr_1_tl_3" n="N003"/>introduction means introduction into the real life of the religious community, in home, society &amp; church.
               <lb facs="#facs_80_tr_1_tl_4" n="N004"/>sont aussi les
               <lb facs="#facs_80_tr_1_tl_5" n="N005"/>de mon ami
               <lb facs="#facs_80_tr_1_tl_6" n="N006"/>dʼune manière
               <lb facs="#facs_80_tr_1_tl_7" n="N007"/>et je mʼai
               <lb facs="#facs_80_tr_1_tl_8" n="N008"/>dʼune manière de
